obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (38389)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content `This Act may be called the Central Vigilance Commission Act, 2003.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069&sectionId=38389&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (38390)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 1 of 2014, s. 58 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 16-1-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069&sectionId=38390&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Central Vigilance Commissioner" means the Central Vigilance Commissioner appointed`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) "Commission" means the Central Vigilance Commission constituted under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 3;`
  line
  line `(c) "Delhi Special Police Establishment" means the Delhi Special Police Establishment`
  line `constituted under sub-section (1) of section 2 of the Delhi Special Police Establishment Act, 1946`
  line `(25 of 1946);`
  line
  line `(d) "Government company" means a Government company within the meaning of the Companies`
  line `Act, 1956 (1 of 1956);`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(da) "Lokpal" means the Lokpal established under sub-section (1) of section 3 of the Lokpal`
  line `and Lokayuktas Act, 2013 (1 of 2014);]`
  line
  line `(e) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) "Vigilance Commissioner" means a Vigilance Commissioner appointed under sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 4.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (38391)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Constitution of Central Vigilance Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069&sectionId=38391&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be constituted a body to be`
  line `known as the Central Vigilance Commission to exercise the powers conferred upon, and to perform the`
  line `functions assigned to it under this Act and the Central Vigilance Commission constituted under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 3 of the Central Vigilance Commission Ordinance, 1999 (Ord. 4 of 1999) which`
  line `ceased to operate, and continued under the Government of India in the Ministry of Personnel, Public`
  line `Grievances and Pensions (Department of Personnel and Training) Resolution No. 371/20/99-AVD. III,`
  line `dated the 4th April, 1999 as amended vide Resolution of even number, dated the 13th August, 2002 shall`
  line `be deemed to be the Commission constituted under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall consist of--`
  line
  line `(a) a Central Vigilance Commissioner -- Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(b) not more than two Vigilance Commissioners -- Members.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Vigilance Commissioner and the Vigilance Commissioners shall be appointed from`
  line `amongst persons--`
  line
  line `(a) who have been or are in an All-India Service or in any civil service of the Union or in a civil`
  line `post under the Union having knowledge and experience in the matters relating to vigilance, policy`
  line `making and administration including police administration; or`
  line
  line `(b) who have held office or are holding office in a corporation established by or under any`
  line `Central Act or a Government company owned or controlled by the Central Government and persons`
  line `who have expertise and experience in finance including insurance and banking, law, vigilance and`
  line `investigations:`
  line
  line `Provided that, from amongst the Central Vigilance Commissioner and the Vigilance Commissioners,`
  line `not more than two persons shall belong to the category of persons referred to either in clause (a) or clause`
  line `(b).`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government shall appoint a Secretary to the Commission on such terms and`
  line `conditions as it deems fit to exercise such powers and discharge such duties as the Commission may by`
  line `regulations specify in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Vigilance Commissioner, the other Vigilance Commissioners and the Secretary to the`
  line `Commission appointed under the Central Vigilance Commission Ordinance, 1999 (Ord. 4 of 1999) or the`
  line `Resolution of the Government of India in the Ministry of Personnel, Public Grievances and Pensions`
  line `(Department of Personnel and Training) Resolution No. 371/20/99-AVD. III, dated the 4th April, 1999 as`
  line `amended vide Resolution of even number, dated the 13th August, 2002 shall be deemed to have been`
  line `appointed under this Act on the same terms and conditions including the term of office subject to which`
  line `they were so appointed under the said Ordinance or the Resolution, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, the expression "term of office" shall be construed`
  line `as the term of office with effect from the date the Central Vigilance Commissioner or any Vigilance`
  line `Commissioner has entered upon his office and continued as such under this Act.`
  line
  line `(6) The headquarters of the Commission shall be at New Delhi.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (38392)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Appointment of Central Vigilance Commissioner and Vigilance Commissioners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069&sectionId=38392&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Central Vigilance Commissioner and the Vigilance Commissioners shall be appointed by the President by`
  line `warrant under his hand and seal:`
  line
  line `Provided that every appointment under this sub-section shall be made after obtaining the`
  line `recommendation of a Committee consisting of--`
  line
  line `(a) the Prime Minister -- Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(b) the Minister of Home Affairs -- Member;`
  line
  line `(c) the Leader of the Opposition in the House of the People -- Member.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, "the Leader of the Opposition in the House of the`
  line `People" shall, when no such Leader has been so recognised, include the Leader of the single largest group`
  line `in opposition of the Government in the House of the People.`
  line
  line `(2) No appointment of a Central Vigilance Commissioner or a Vigilance Commissioner shall be`
  line `invalid merely by reason of any vacancy in the Committee.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (38393)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Terms and other conditions of service of Central Vigilance Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069&sectionId=38393&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the`
  line `provisions of sub-sections (3) and (4), the Central Vigilance Commissioner shall hold office for a term of`
  line `four years from the date on which he enters upon his office or till he attains the age of sixty-five years,`
  line `whichever is earlier. The Central Vigilance Commissioner, on ceasing to hold the office, shall be`
  line `ineligible for reappointment in the Commission.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of sub-sections (3) and (4), every Vigilance Commissioner shall hold`
  line `office for a term of four years from the date on which he enters upon his office or till he attains the age of`
  line `sixty-five years, whichever is earlier:`
  line
  line `Provided that every Vigilance Commissioner, on ceasing to hold the office, shall be eligible for`
  line `appointment as the Central Vigilance Commissioner in the manner specified in sub-section (1) of section`
  line `4:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the term of the Vigilance Commissioner, if appointed as the Central Vigilance`
  line `Commissioner, shall not be more than four years in aggregate as the Vigilance Commissioner and the`
  line `Central Vigilance Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Vigilance Commissioner or a Vigilance Commissioner shall, before he enters upon`
  line `his office, make and subscribe before the President, or some other person appointed in that behalf by him,`
  line `an oath or affirmation according to the form set out for the purpose in Schedule to this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Vigilance Commissioner or a Vigilance Commissioner may, by writing under his`
  line `hand addressed to the President, resign his office.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Vigilance Commissioner or a Vigilance Commissioner may be removed from his`
  line `office in the manner provided in section 6.`
  line
  line `(6) On ceasing to hold office, the Central Vigilance Commissioner and every other Vigilance`
  line `Commissioner shall be ineligible for--`
  line
  line `(a) any diplomatic assignment, appointment as administrator of a Union territory and such other`
  line `assignment or appointment which is required by law to be made by the President by warrant under his`
  line `hand and seal;`
  line
  line `(b) further employment to any office of profit under the Government of India or the Government`
  line `of a State.`
  line
  line `(7) The salary and allowances payable to and the other conditions of service of--`
  line
  line `(a) the Central Vigilance Commissioner shall be the same as those of the Chairman of the Union`
  line `Public Service Commission;`
  line
  line `(b) the Vigilance Commissioner shall be the same as those of a Member of the Union Public`
  line `Service Commission:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Central Vigilance Commissioner or any Vigilance Commissioner is, at the time of`
  line `his appointment, in receipt of a pension (other than a disability or wound pension) in respect of any`
  line `previous service under the Government of India or under the Government of a State, his salary in respect`
  line `of the service as the Central Vigilance Commissioner or any Vigilance Commissioner shall be reduced by`
  line `the amount of that pension including any portion of pension which was commuted and pension equivalent`
  line `of other forms of retirement benefits excluding pension equivalent of retirement gratuity:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if the Central Vigilance Commissioner or any Vigilance Commissioner is, at the`
  line `time of his appointment, in receipt of retirement benefits in respect of any previous service rendered in a`
  line `corporation established by or under any Central Act or a Government company owned or controlled by`
  line `the Central Government, his salary in respect of the service as the Central Vigilance Commissioner or, as`
  line `the case may be, the Vigilance Commissioner shall be reduced by the amount of pension equivalent to the`
  line `retirement benefits:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the salary, allowances and pension payable to, and the other conditions of service`
  line `of, the Central Vigilance Commissioner or any Vigilance Commissioner shall not be varied to his`
  line `disadvantage after his appointment.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (38394)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Removal of Central Vigilance Commissioner and Vigilance Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069&sectionId=38394&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (3), the Central Vigilance Commissioner or any Vigilance Commissioner shall`
  line `be removed from his office only by order of the President on the ground of proved misbehaviour or`
  line `incapacity after the Supreme Court, on a reference made to it by the President, has, on inquiry, reported`
  line `that the Central Vigilance Commissioner or any Vigilance Commissioner, as the case may be, ought on`
  line `such ground be removed.`
  line
  line `(2) The President may suspend from office, and if deem necessary prohibit also from attending the`
  line `office during inquiry, the Central Vigilance Commissioner or any Vigilance Commissioner in respect of`
  line `whom a reference has been made to the Supreme Court under sub-section (1) until the President has`
  line `passed orders on receipt of the report of the Supreme Court on such reference.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the President may by order remove from`
  line `office the Central Vigilance Commissioner or any Vigilance Commissioner if the Central Vigilance`
  line `Commissioner or such Vigilance Commissioner, as the case may be,--`
  line
  line `(a) is adjudged an insolvent; or`
  line
  line `(b) has been convicted of an offence which, in the opinion of the Central Government, involves`
  line `moral turpitude; or`
  line
  line `(c) engages during his term of office in any paid employment outside the duties of his office; or`
  line
  line `(d) is, in the opinion of the President, unfit to continue in office by reason of infirmity of mind or`
  line `body; or`
  line
  line `(e) has acquired such financial or other interest as is likely to affect prejudicially his functions as`
  line `a Central Vigilance Commissioner or a Vigilance Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(4) If the Central Vigilance Commissioner or any Vigilance Commissioner is or becomes in any way,`
  line `concerned or interested in any contract or agreement made by or on behalf of the Government of India or`
  line `participates in any way in the profit thereof or in any benefit or emolument arising therefrom otherwise`
  line `than as a member and in common with the other members of an incorporated company, he shall, for the`
  line `purposes of sub-section (1), be deemed to be guilty of misbehaviour.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (38395)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Power to make rules by Central Government for staff.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069&sectionId=38395&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, in`
  line `consultation with the Commission, make rules with respect to the number of members of the staff of the`
  line `Commission and their conditions of service.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (38396)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Functions and powers of Central Vigilance Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 1 of 2014, s. 58 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 16-1-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069&sectionId=38396&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The functions and powers of the`
  line `Commission shall be to--`
  line
  line `(a) exercise superintendence over the functioning of the Delhi Special Police Establishment in so`
  line `far as it relates to the investigation of offences alleged to have been committed under the Prevention`
  line `of Corruption Act, 1988 (49 of 1988) or an offence with which a public servant specified in`
  line `sub-section (2) may, under the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), be charged at the same`
  line trial;
  line
  line `(b) give directions to the Delhi Special Police Establishment for the purpose of discharging the`
  line `responsibility entrusted to it under sub-section (1) of section 4 of the Delhi Special Police`
  line `Establishment Act, 1946 (25 of 1946):`
  line
  line `Provided that while exercising the powers of superintendence under clause (a) or giving`
  line `directions under this clause, the Commission shall not exercise powers in such a manner so as to`
  line `require the Delhi Special Police Establishment to investigate or dispose of any case in a particular`
  line manner;
  line
  line `(c) inquire or cause an inquiry or investigation to be made on a reference made by the Central`
  line `Government wherein it is alleged that a public servant being an employee of the Central Government`
  line `or a corporation established by or under any Central Act, Government company, society and any local`
  line `authority owned or controlled by that Government, has committed an offence under the Prevention of`
  line `Corruption Act, 1988 (49 of 1988) or an offence with which a public servant may, under the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), be charged at the same trial;`
  line
  line `(d) inquire or cause an inquiry or investigation to be made into any complaint against any official`
  line `belonging to such category of officials specified in sub-section (2) wherein it is alleged that he has`
  line `committed an offence under the Prevention of Corruption Act, 1988 (49 of 1988) and an offence with`
  line `which a public servant specified in sub-section (2) may, under the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973`
  line `(2 of 1974), be charged at the same trial;`
  line
  line `(e) review the progress of investigations conducted by the Delhi Special Police Establishment`
  line `into offences alleged to have been committed under the Prevention of Corruption Act, 1988`
  line `(49 of 1988) or the public servant may, under the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), be`
  line `charged at the same trial;`
  line
  line `(f) review the progress of applications pending with the competent authorities for sanction of`
  line `prosecution under the Prevention of Corruption Act, 1988 (49 of 1988);`
  line
  line `(g) tender advice to the Central Government, corporations established by or under any Central`
  line `Act, Government companies, societies and local authorities owned or controlled by the Central`
  line `Government on such matters as may be referred to it by that Government, said Government`
  line `companies, societies and local authorities owned or controlled by the Central Government or`
  line otherwise;
  line
  line `(h) exercise superintendence over the vigilance administration of the various Ministries of the`
  line `Central Government or corporations established by or under any Central Act, Government`
  line `companies, societies and local authorities owned or controlled by that Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this clause shall be deemed to authorise the Commission to`
  line `exercise superintendence over the Vigilance administration in a manner not consistent with the`
  line `directions relating to vigilance matters issued by the Government and to confer power upon the`
  line `Commission to issue directions relating to any policy matters.`
  line
  line `(2) The persons referred to in clause (d) of sub-section (1) are as follows:--`
  line
  line `(a) members of All-India Services serving in connection with the affairs of the Union and Group`
  line `'A' officers of the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) such level of officers of the corporations established by or under any Central Act, Government`
  line `companies, societies and other local authorities, owned or controlled by the Central Government, as`
  line `that Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf:`
  line
  line `Provided that till such time a notification is issued under this clause, all officers of the said`
  line `corporations, companies, societies and local authorities shall be deemed to be the persons referred to`
  line `in clause (d) of sub-section (1);`
  line
  line `^1[(c) on a reference made by the Lokpal under the proviso to sub-section (1) of section 20 of the`
  line `Lokpal and Lokayuktas Act, 2013 (1 of 2014), the persons referred to in clause (d) of sub-section (1)`
  line `shall also include--`
  line
  line `(i) members of Group B, Group C and Group D services of the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(ii) such level of officials or staff of the corporations established by or under any Central Act,`
  line `Government companies, societies and other local authorities, owned or controlled by the Central`
  line `Government, as that Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this`
  line `behalf:`
  line
  line `Provided that till such time a notification is issued under this clause, all officials or staff of the said`
  line `corporations, companies, societies and local authorities shall be deemed to be the persons referred in`
  line `clause (d) of sub-section (1).]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_a:
  sectionId (38397)
  sectionNo 8A
  orderNo 9
  title `Action on preliminary inquiry in relation to public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 1 of 2014, s. 58 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 16-1-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069&sectionId=38397&sectionno=8A&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069
obj_root_law_sections_8_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[8A. Action on preliminary inquiry in relation to public servants.-- (1) Where, after the`
  line `conclusion of the preliminary inquiry relating to corruption of public servants belonging to Group C and`
  line `Group D officials of the Central Government, the findings of the Commission disclose, after giving an`
  line `opportunity of being heard to the public servant, a prima facie violation of conduct rules relating to`
  line `corruption under the Prevention of Corruption Act, 1988 (49 of 1988) by such public servant, the`
  line `Commission shall proceed with one or more of the following actions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) cause an investigation by any agency or the Delhi Special Police Establishment, as the case`
  line `may be;`
  line
  line `(b) initiation of the disciplinary proceedings or any other appropriate action against the concerned`
  line `public servant by the competent authority;`
  line
  line `(c) closure of the proceedings against the public servant and to proceed against the complainant`
  line `under section 46 of the Lokpal and Lokayuktas Act, 2013 (1 of 2014).`
  line
  line `(2) Every preliminary inquiry referred to in sub-section (1) shall ordinarily be completed within a`
  line `period of ninety days and for reasons to be recorded in writing, within a further period of ninety days`
  line `from the date of receipt of the complaint.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_b:
  sectionId (38398)
  sectionNo 8B
  orderNo 10
  title `Action on investigation in relation to public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 1 of 2014, s. 58 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 16-1-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069&sectionId=38398&sectionno=8B&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069
obj_root_law_sections_8_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[8B. Action on investigation in relation to public servants.--(1) In case the Commission decides to`
  line `proceed to investigate into the complaint under clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 8A, it shall direct`
  line `any agency (including the Delhi Special Police Establishment) to carry out the investigation as`
  line `expeditiously as possible and complete the investigation within a period of six months from the date of its order and submit the investigation report containing its findings to the Commission:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Commission may extend the said period by a further period of six months for the`
  line `reasons to be recorded in writing.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 173 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973`
  line `(2 of 1974), any agency (including the Delhi Special Police Establishment) shall, in respect of cases`
  line `referred to it by the Commission, submit the investigation report to the Commission.`
  line
  line `(3) The Commission shall consider every report received by it under sub-section (2) from any agency`
  line `(including the Delhi Special Police Establishment) and may decide as to--`
  line
  line `(a) file charge-sheet or closure report before the Special Court against the public servant;`
  line
  line `(b) initiate the departmental proceedings or any other appropriate action against the concerned`
  line `public servant by the competent authority.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (38399)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 11
  title `Proceedings of Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069&sectionId=38399&sectionno=9&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The proceedings of the Commission shall be conducted at its`
  line headquarters.
  line
  line `(2) The Commission may, by unanimous decision, regulate the procedure for transaction of its`
  line `business as also allocation of its business amongst the Central Vigilance Commissioner and other`
  line `Vigilance Commissioners.`
  line
  line `(3) Save as provided in sub-section (2), all business of the Commission shall, as far as possible, be`
  line `transacted unanimously.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (3), if the Central Vigilance Commissioner and other`
  line `Vigilance Commissioners differ in opinion on any matter, such matter shall be decided according to the`
  line `opinion of the majority.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Vigilance Commissioner, or, if for any reason he is unable to attend any meeting of`
  line `the Commission, the senior-most Vigilance Commissioner present at the meeting, shall preside at the`
  line meeting.
  line
  line `(6) No act or proceeding of the Commission shall be invalid merely by reason of--`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the Commission; or`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the appointment of a person acting as the Central Vigilance Commissioner or as`
  line `a Vigilance Commissioner; or`
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in the procedure of the Commission not affecting the merits of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (38400)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 12
  title `Vigilance Commissioner to act as Central Vigilance Commissioner in certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069&sectionId=38400&sectionno=10&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the event of the occurrence of any vacancy in the office of the Central Vigilance`
  line `Commissioner by reason of his death, resignation or otherwise, the President may, by notification,`
  line `authorise one of the Vigilance Commissioners to act as the Central Vigilance Commissioner until the`
  line `appointment of a new Central Vigilance Commissioner to fill such vacancy.`
  line
  line `(2) When the Central Vigilance Commissioner is unable to discharge his functions owing to absence`
  line `on leave or otherwise, such one of the Vigilance Commissioners as the President may, by notification,`
  line `authorise in this behalf, shall discharge the functions of the Central Vigilance Commissioner until the date`
  line `on which the Central Vigilance Commissioner resumes his duties.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (38401)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 13
  title `Power relating to inquiries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069&sectionId=38401&sectionno=11&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `The Commission shall, while conducting any inquiry referred to in`
  line `clauses (b) and (c) of sub-section (1) of section 8, have all the powers of a civil court trying a suit under`
  line `the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) and in particular, in respect of the following matters,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person from any part of India and examining`
  line `him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of any document;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) requisitioning any public record or copy thereof from any court or office;`
  line
  line `(e) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or other documents; and`
  line
  line `(f) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11_a:
  sectionId (38402)
  sectionNo 11A
  orderNo 14
  title `Director of Inquiry for making preliminary inquiry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 1 of 2014, s. 58 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 16-1-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069&sectionId=38402&sectionno=11A&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069
obj_root_law_sections_11_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[11A. Director of Inquiry for making preliminary inquiry.--(1) There shall be a Director of`
  line `Inquiry, not below the rank of Joint Secretary to the Government of India, who shall be appointed by the`
  line `Central Government for conducting preliminary inquiries referred to the Commission by the Lokpal.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall provide the Director of Inquiry such officers and employees as may`
  line `be required for the discharge of his functions under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (38403)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 15
  title `Proceedings before Commission to be judicial proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069&sectionId=38403&sectionno=12&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The Commission shall be`
  line `deemed to be a civil court for the purposes of section 195 and Chapter XXVI of the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) and every proceeding before the Commission shall be deemed to be a`
  line `judicial proceeding within the meaning of sections 193 and 228 and for the purposes of section 196 of the`
  line `Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (38404)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 16
  title `Expenses of Commission to be charged on the Consolidated Fund of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069&sectionId=38404&sectionno=13&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `The expenses of`
  line `the Commission, including any salaries, allowances and pensions payable to or in respect of the Central`
  line `Vigilance Commissioner, the Vigilance Commissioners, Secretary and the staff of the Commission, shall`
  line `be charged on the Consolidated Fund of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (38405)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 17
  title `Annual report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069&sectionId=38405&sectionno=14&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the duty of the Commission to present annually to the President a`
  line `report as to the work done by the Commission within six months of the close of the year under report.`
  line
  line `(2) The report referred to in sub-section (1) shall contain a separate part on the functioning of the`
  line `Delhi Special Police Establishment in so far as it relates to sub-section (1) of section 4 of the Delhi`
  line `Special Police Establishment Act, 1946 (25 of 1946).`
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of such report, the President shall cause the same to be laid before each House of`
  line Parliament.
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (38406)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 18
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069&sectionId=38406&sectionno=15&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Commission, the Central Vigilance Commissioner, any Vigilance Commissioner, the`
  line `Secretary or against any staff of the Commission in respect of anything which is in good faith done or`
  line `intended to be done under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (38407)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 19
  title `Central Vigilance Commissioner, Vigilance Commissioner and staff to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069&sectionId=38407&sectionno=16&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The Central Vigilance Commissioner, every Vigilance Commissioner, the Secretary and every staff of the`
  line `Commission shall be deemed to be a public servant within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal`
  line `Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (38408)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 20
  title `Report of any inquiry made on reference by Commission to be forwarded to that Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069&sectionId=38408&sectionno=17&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The report of the inquiry undertaken by any agency on a reference made by the`
  line `Commission shall be forwarded to the Commission.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall, on receipt of such report and after taking into consideration any other`
  line `factors relevant thereto, advise the Central Government and corporations established by or under any`
  line `Central Act, Government companies, societies and local authorities owned or controlled by that`
  line `Government, as the case may be, as to the further course of action.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government and the corporations established by or under any Central Act,`
  line `Government companies, societies and other local authorities owned or controlled by that Government, as`
  line `the case may be, shall consider the advice of the Commission and take appropriate action:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the Central Government, any corporation established by or under any Central`
  line `Act, Government company, society or local authority owned or controlled by the Central Government, as the case may be, does not agree with the advice of the Commission, it shall, for reasons to be recorded in`
  line `writing, communicate the same to the Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (38409)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 21
  title `Power to call for information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069&sectionId=38409&sectionno=18&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The Commission may call for reports, returns and statements`
  line `from the Central Government or corporations established by or under any Central Act, Government`
  line `companies, societies and other local authorities owned or controlled by that Government so as to enable it`
  line `to exercise general supervision over the vigilance and anti-corruption work in that Government and in the`
  line `said corporations, Government companies, societies and local authorities.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (38410)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 22
  title `Consultation with Commission in certain matters.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069&sectionId=38410&sectionno=19&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall, in making`
  line `any rules or regulations governing the vigilance or disciplinary matters relating to persons appointed to`
  line `public services and posts in connection with the affairs of the Union or to members of the All-India`
  line `Services, consult the Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (38411)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 23
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069&sectionId=38411&sectionno=20&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for the purpose of carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the number of members of the staff and their conditions of service under section 7;`
  line
  line `(b) any other power of the civil court to be prescribed under clause (f) of section 11; and`
  line
  line `(c) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (38412)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 24
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069&sectionId=38412&sectionno=21&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission may, with the previous approval of the`
  line `Central Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, make regulations not inconsistent with this`
  line `Act and the rules made thereunder to provide for all matters for which provision is expedient for the`
  line `purposes of giving effect to the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the duties and the powers of the Secretary under sub-section (4) of section 3; and`
  line
  line `(b) the procedure to be followed by the Commission under sub-section (2) of section 9.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (38413)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 25
  title `Notification, rule, etc., to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069&sectionId=38413&sectionno=22&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Every notification issued under clause`
  line `(b) of sub-section (2) of section 8 and every rule made by the Central Government and every regulation`
  line `made by the Commission under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is issued or made, before`
  line `each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised`
  line `in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the notification or the rule or the regulation, or both Houses agree that the notification or the rule or the`
  line `regulation should not be made, the notification or the rule or the regulation shall thereafter have effect`
  line `only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification`
  line `or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that notification`
  line `or rule or regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (38414)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 26
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069&sectionId=38414&sectionno=23&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order, not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, remove`
  line `the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of two years from the date of`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall, as soon as may be after it is made, be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (38415)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 27
  title `Provisions relating to existing Vigilance Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069&sectionId=38415&sectionno=24&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `With effect from the constitution of the`
  line `Commission under sub-section (1) of section 3, the Central Vigilance Commission set up by the`
  line `Resolution of the Government of India in the Ministry of Home Affairs No. 24/7/64-AVD, dated the 11th`
  line `February, 1964 (hereafter referred to in this section as the existing Vigilance Commission) shall, insofar as its functions are not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, continue to discharge the said`
  line `functions and--`
  line
  line `(a) all actions and decisions taken by the Vigilance Commission insofar as such actions and`
  line `decisions are relatable to the functions of the Commission constituted under this Act shall be deemed`
  line `to have been taken by the Commission;`
  line
  line `(b) all proceedings pending before the Vigilance Commission, insofar as such proceedings relate`
  line `to the functions of the Commission, shall be deemed to be transferred to the Commission and shall be`
  line `dealt with in accordance with the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) the employees of the Vigilance Commission shall be deemed to have become the employees`
  line `of the Commission on the same terms and conditions;`
  line
  line `(d) all the assets and liabilities of the Vigilance Commission shall be transferred to the`
  line Commission.
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (38416)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 28
  title `Appointments, etc., of officers of Directorate of Enforcement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 46 of 2021, s. 2 (w.e.f. 14-11-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069&sectionId=38416&sectionno=25&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in the Foreign Exchange Management Act, 1999 (42 of 1999) or any other law for the time`
  line `being in force,--`
  line
  line `(a) the Central Government shall appoint a Director of Enforcement in the Directorate of`
  line `Enforcement in the Ministry of Finance on the recommendation of the Committee consisting of--`
  line
  line `(i) the Central Vigilance Commissioner -- Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(ii) Vigilance Commissioners -- Members;`
  line
  line `(iii) Secretary to the Government of India in-charge of the Ministry of Home Affairs in the`
  line `Central Government -- Member;`
  line
  line `(iv) Secretary to the Government of India in-charge of the Ministry of Personnel in the`
  line `Central Government -- Member;`
  line
  line `(v) Secretary to the Government of India in-charge of the Department of Revenue, Ministry`
  line `of Finance in the Central Government -- Member;`
  line
  line `(b) while making a recommendation, the Committee shall take into consideration the integrity and`
  line `experience of the officers eligible for appointment;`
  line
  line `(c) no person below the rank of Additional Secretary to the Government of India shall be eligible`
  line `for appointment as a Director of Enforcement;`
  line
  line `(d) a Director of Enforcement shall continue to hold office for a period of not less than two years from the date on which he assumes office;`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that the period for which the Director of Enforcement holds the office on his initial appointment may, in public interest, on the recommendation of the Committee under clause (a) and for the reasons to be recorded in writing, be extended up to one year at a time:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no such extension shall be granted after the completion of a period of five years in total including the period mentioned in the initial appointment; ]`
  line
  line `(e) a Director of Enforcement shall not be transferred except with the previous consent of the`
  line `Committee referred to in clause (a);`
  line
  line `(f) the Committee referred to in clause (a) shall, in consultation with the Director of Enforcement,`
  line `recommend officers for appointment to the posts above the level of the Deputy Director of`
  line `Enforcement and also recommend the extension or curtailment of the tenure of such officers in the`
  line `Directorate of Enforcement;`
  line
  line `(g) on receipt of the recommendation under clause (f), the Central Government shall pass such`
  line `orders as it thinks fit to give effect to the said recommendation.`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (38417)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 29
  title `Amendment of Act 25 of 1946.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069&sectionId=38417&sectionno=26&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00005_200345_1517807323069
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `In the Delhi Special Police Establishment Act, 1946,--`
  line
  line `(a) after section 1, the following section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `1A. Interpretation section.--Words and expressions used herein and not defined but`
  line `defined in the Central Vigilance Commission Act, 2003 (45 of 2003), shall have the meanings,`
  line `respectively, assigned to them in that Act.;`
  line
  line `(b) for section 4, the following sections shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `4. Superintendence and administration of Special Police Establishment.--(1) The`
  line `superintendence of the Delhi Special Police Establishment in so far as it relates to investigation of offences alleged to have been committed under the Prevention of Corruption Act, 1988`
  line `(49 of 1988), shall vest in the Commission.`
  line
  line `(2) Save as otherwise provided in sub-section (1), the superintendence of the said police`
  line `establishment in all other matters shall vest in the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The administration of the said police establishment shall vest in an officer appointed in`
  line `this behalf by the Central Government (hereinafter referred to as the Director) who shall exercise`
  line `in respect of that police establishment such of the powers exercisable by an Inspector-General of`
  line `Police in respect of the police force in a State as the Central Government may specify in this`
  line behalf.
  line
  line `4A. Committee for appointment of Director.--(1) The Central Government shall appoint`
  line `the Director on the recommendation of the Committee consisting of--`
  line
  line `(a) the Central Vigilance Commissioner -- Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(b) Vigilance Commissioners -- Members;`
  line
  line `(c) Secretary to the Government of India in-charge of the Ministry of Home Affairs in the`
  line `Central Government`
  line `-- Member;`
  line
  line `(d) Secretary (Coordination and Public`
  line `Grievances) in the Cabinet Secretariat`
  line `-- Member.`
  line
  line `(2) While making any recommendation under sub-section (1), the Committee shall take into`
  line `consideration the views of the outgoing Director.`
  line
  line `(3) The Committee shall recommend a panel of officers--`
  line
  line `(a) on the basis of seniority, integrity and experience in the investigation of anticorruption cases; and`
  line
  line `(b) chosen from amongst officers belonging to the Indian Police Service constituted`
  line `under the All-India Services Act, 1951 (61 of 1951),`
  line `for being considered for appointment as the Director.`
  line
  line `4B. Terms and conditions of service of Director.--(1) The Director shall, notwithstanding`
  line `anything to the contrary contained in the rules relating to his conditions of service, continue to`
  line `hold office for a period of not less than two years from the date on which he assumes office.`
  line
  line `(2) The Director shall not be transferred except with the previous consent of the Committee`
  line `referred to in sub-section (1) of section 4A.`
  line
  line `4C. Appointment for posts of Superintendent of Police and above, extension and`
  line `curtailment of their tenure, etc.--(1) The Committee referred to in section 4A shall, after`
  line `consulting the Director, recommend officers for appointment to the posts of the level of`
  line `Superintendent of Police and above and also recommend the extension or curtailment of the`
  line `tenure of such officers in the Delhi Special Police Establishment.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of the recommendation under sub-section (1), the Central Government shall`
  line `pass such orders as it thinks fit to give effect to the said recommendation.;`
  line
  line `(c) after section 6, the following section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `6A. Approval of Central Government to conduct inquiry or investigation.--(1) The`
  line `Delhi Special Police Establishment shall not conduct any inquiry or investigation into any offence`
  line `alleged to have been committed under the Prevention of Corruption Act, 1988 (49 of 1988)`
  line `except with the previous approval of the Central Government where such allegation relates to--`
  line
  line `(a) the employees of the Central Government of the level of Joint Secretary and above;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) such officers as are appointed by the Central Government in corporations established`
  line `by or under any Central Act, Government companies, societies and local authorities owned or`
  line `controlled by that Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), no such approval shall be`
  line `necessary for cases involving arrest of a person on the spot on the charge of accepting or`
  line `attempting to accept any gratification other than legal remuneration referred to in clause (c) of the`
  line `Explanation to section 7 of the Prevention of Corruption Act, 1988 (49 of 1988)..`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
